{"id":417682274,"lang":"python3","time":"7 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1604740847,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"64 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/417682274/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers II","memory":"14.1 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n#         self.val = val\n#         self.next = next\nclass Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        num1 = 0\n        while l1:\n            num1 = (num1 * 10) + l1.val\n            l1 = l1.next\n        num2 = 0\n        while l2:\n            num2 = (num2 * 10) + l2.val\n            l2 = l2.next\n        total = num1 + num2\n        if total == 0:\n            return ListNode(0)\n\n        node = None\n        while total > 0:\n            node = ListNode(total % 10, node)\n            total //= 10\n        return node","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers-ii"}
